quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  11,82,"So, when Our command came, We turned its highest into the lowest, and We rained on it stones of hard clay, one over another"
  11,83,"marked, with your Lord. And it is not far from the transgressors."
  11,84,"And to Madyan (We sent) their brother, Shu'aib. He said, "0 my people, worship Allah. You have no god other than Him. And do not lessen the measure and the weight. I see you quite well off, and I fear for you the punishment of an encircling day."
  11,85,"And 0 my people, perfect the measure and the balance with justice and do not make the people short of their things, and do not go about the earth spreading disorder."
  11,86,"Whatever is left (with you) by Allah is better for you, if you are believers. And I am not a watchman over you."
  11,87,"They said, "0 Shu'aib, does your galah (prayer) command you that we should give up what our fathers used to worship or give up our free-will in (spending) our wealth? You are provenly the man of wisdom and guidance.""
  11,88,"He said, "0 my people, tell me, if I am on a clear path from my Lord and He has provided me from Himself with a good provision, (should I still leave you unguided?) And I do not want to do in your absence what I prohibit for you. I want nothing but to set things right as far as I can. .And my ability to do things comes from none but Allah. In Him alone I have placed my trust and to Him alone I turn in humbleness."